<link href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4378&amp;p=6146#p6146"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Hierarchical checkboxes / Interdependent checkboxes]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4378&amp;p=6146#p6146"><![CDATA[
There is a thing, I'm missing in HTML for a very long time. I think I've read this somewhere here, but I don't find it.<br /><br />What I would like very much is the possibility to have checkboxes / radiobuttons that control other checkboxes / radiobuttons.<br /><br />For example I activate (deactivate) one checkbox and this activates (deactivates) other checkboxes too.<br /><br />I know that such hierarchical / interdependent checkboxes are possible with Scripting. But for those who have Scripting deactivated (and maybe even cannot change this, e.g. at work or school) that isn't an option.<br /><br />This feature should be possible only with HTML and CSS!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1367">Gabor</a> — Thu Aug 05, 2010 11:18 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
